# es_event_settime_t

**Structure**

A type for an event that indicates the modification of the system time.

## Declaration

```swift
struct es_event_settime_t
```

## Overview

The system doesn’t generate this event if the source app contains the entitlement `com.apple.private.settime`.

Even if an Endpoint Security client responds to an [doc://com.apple.endpointsecurity/documentation/EndpointSecurity/ES_EVENT_TYPE_AUTH_SETTIME] event with [doc://com.apple.endpointsecurity/documentation/EndpointSecurity/ES_AUTH_RESULT_ALLOW], the operation may still fail. For example, the process used to set the time may lack sufficient privileges.

## Inspecting Event Properties

- **reserved**: An unused field reserved for future use.

## Initializers

- **init()**
- **init(reserved:)**

## Conforms To

- BitwiseCopyable
- Sendable
